text:
Other enrichments

In a standard GO analysis of neuron+spermatid genes vs all neuron genes, we find a significant 44% enrichment of “cytosol genes” and “extracellular exosome genes” are twice as frequent in neuron+spermatid as in neuron genes. Chromatin genes are completely absent in neuron+spermatid

These neuron+spermatid cytosol genes are enriched for both xi-escapers and deltaE genes.

XCI among cytosol enriched: {‘DDX3X’, ‘EIF2S3’, ‘HUWE1’, ‘RAB9A’, ‘RPS4X’, ‘SYAP1’, ‘UBA1’}

deltaE among cytosol enriched: {‘DDX3X’, ‘EIF1AX’, ‘FMR1’, ‘GDI1’, ‘GRIPAP1’, ‘PUDP’, ‘RBBP7’, ‘SMC1A’, ‘SYAP1’, ‘TBC1D8B’, ‘TMSB4X’, ‘UBA1’}

iPsych found TSPAN7 and SLC25A14 genes.
